Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says the department will conduct its own report on Enoch Mpianzi's death, which will be released in three months. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says the department will conduct its own report on Enoch Mpianzi's death, which will be released in three months. The 13-year-old Parktown Boys' High School pupil fell into a river when the makeshift raft he was in, overturned during a school camp in Brits in the North West. WATCH: Lesufi speaks on the death of Parktown Boys pupil Lesufi says it will also indicate who should be held accountable. “We are devastated at the department...and will do everything in our power to compile a proper report,” Lesufi said. Police have opened an inquest into Mpianzi's death.